1
00:00:03,083 --> 00:00:05,916
(power saw whirring)

2
00:00:12,359 --> 00:00:14,293
Hurry and get him out of there!

3
00:00:16,029 --> 00:00:18,190
I need two men
on the left side now.

4
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:22,200
Wait. Where you
goin' with him?

5
00:00:22,269 --> 00:00:23,429
He's dead.

6
00:00:23,503 --> 00:00:24,561
There's a woman
over there who isn't

7
00:00:24,638 --> 00:00:26,538
and she needs some oxygen.

8
00:00:40,754 --> 00:00:43,314
Boy: I want you to rise!

9
00:00:43,390 --> 00:00:45,221
Rise up and heal!

10
00:00:45,292 --> 00:00:46,623
What the hell you doing?

11
00:00:46,693 --> 00:00:48,126
Boy's laying on hands.

12
00:00:48,195 --> 00:00:49,287
Rise up

13
00:00:49,363 --> 00:00:50,660
and accept the miracle

14
00:00:50,731 --> 00:00:52,892
He's given you.

15
00:00:52,966 --> 00:00:54,831
You don't understand.
The man's dead.

16
00:00:54,901 --> 00:00:59,099
Then the boy can't possibly
do any harm, can he?

17
00:00:59,172 --> 00:01:00,264
For this

18
00:01:00,340 --> 00:01:01,967
is the power of belief--

19
00:01:02,075 --> 00:01:05,442
the power to separate
the light from the darkness

20
00:01:05,512 --> 00:01:07,810
to create life from death.

21
00:01:07,881 --> 00:01:09,280
Amen.

22
00:01:09,349 --> 00:01:11,749
Show's over!

23
00:01:11,818 --> 00:01:13,911
Let's clear the area.

24
00:01:29,269 --> 00:01:32,067
Hallelujah, Samuel.
Hallelujah.

25
00:02:20,287 --> 00:02:23,620
(singing gospel)

26
00:02:30,764 --> 00:02:32,994
Yes, indeed, praise God!

27
00:02:33,066 --> 00:02:36,399
Yes! Yes! Yes!

28
00:02:36,470 --> 00:02:38,768
I want everybody
to say hallelujah!

29
00:02:38,839 --> 00:02:39,771
(congregation:)
Hallelujah!

30
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,967
Praise the Lord!

31
00:02:42,042 --> 00:02:46,809
The woman on the table has
a malignant tumor on her spine.

32
00:02:46,913 --> 00:02:48,471
This boy here will attempt

33
00:02:48,582 --> 00:02:50,880
to heal her by simply
laying his hands on her.

34
00:02:50,951 --> 00:02:52,316
Where did you get this?

35
00:02:52,385 --> 00:02:54,717
From the regional office
in Tennessee.

36
00:02:54,788 --> 00:02:56,415
The preacher's name is...

37
00:02:56,490 --> 00:02:57,889
Reverend Calvin Hartley.

38
00:02:57,958 --> 00:02:59,516
You've heard ofhim.

39
00:02:59,593 --> 00:03:01,493
The boy is his adopted son, Samuel.

40
00:03:01,561 --> 00:03:03,756
He claims to have found him
as an infant

41
00:03:03,830 --> 00:03:06,697
Iying in the tall weeds
near the muddy Mississippi.

42
00:03:06,766 --> 00:03:09,894
He also claims the boy brought
a man back from the dead.

43
00:03:09,970 --> 00:03:11,369
It's more than a claim.

44
00:03:11,438 --> 00:03:14,373
The man he saved appears
as a regular attraction

45
00:03:14,441 --> 00:03:16,409
in the reverend's tent ministry.

46
00:03:16,510 --> 00:03:18,501
The boy's been
performing miracles

47
00:03:18,612 --> 00:03:20,807
every week for the past ten years,
twice on Sunday.

48
00:03:20,914 --> 00:03:23,576
Not according to the Kenwood sheriff.

49
00:03:23,683 --> 00:03:24,877
Local authorities think

50
00:03:24,951 --> 00:03:28,284
Reverend Hartley and his son
are a scam.

51
00:03:28,355 --> 00:03:30,118
They've been trying
to shut them down

52
00:03:30,190 --> 00:03:31,680
but without any luck.

53
00:03:31,758 --> 00:03:33,749
They've turned to the FBI
to try and get a prosecution.

54
00:03:33,827 --> 00:03:35,351
Forwhat? Fraud?

55
00:03:35,428 --> 00:03:36,895
No. Murder.

56
00:03:36,963 --> 00:03:39,090
Watch the tape.

57
00:03:39,165 --> 00:03:42,032
Lucy Kelly has the cancer.

58
00:03:42,102 --> 00:03:45,663
Her doctors say it is inoperable.

59
00:03:45,739 --> 00:03:48,606
They say it is incurable.

60
00:03:48,675 --> 00:03:50,267
But I say to you

61
00:03:50,377 --> 00:03:53,835
that what the doctors cannot cure

62
00:03:53,947 --> 00:03:55,175
the Lord can.

63
00:03:55,282 --> 00:03:56,579
(congregation:)
Amen!

64
00:03:56,650 --> 00:03:58,174
Yes, indeed. Praise God.

65
00:03:58,285 --> 00:04:00,185
Because God...

66
00:04:00,253 --> 00:04:03,120
can work... miracles.

67
00:04:03,189 --> 00:04:04,918
- Yes, Lord.
- Praise God.

68
00:04:04,991 --> 00:04:09,428
The clear light
of God's healing love...

69
00:04:09,496 --> 00:04:10,929
is fowing...

70
00:04:10,997 --> 00:04:15,991
through Samuel's healing hands...

71
00:04:16,069 --> 00:04:19,004
20 minutes later, Lucy Kelly
was rushed to the hospital.

72
00:04:19,072 --> 00:04:20,596
She was pronounced dead on arrival.

73
00:04:20,674 --> 00:04:22,039
What caused her death?

74
00:04:22,108 --> 00:04:24,906
I don't know,
but it wasn't cancer.

75
00:04:25,011 --> 00:04:26,945
They've requested someone

76
00:04:27,013 --> 00:04:29,880
with a medical background
to assist local police.

77
00:04:29,950 --> 00:04:31,508
I know it's not an X file...

78
00:04:31,618 --> 00:04:33,552
When do we leave for Tennessee?

79
00:04:42,929 --> 00:04:46,865
I think I saw some of
these same people at Woodstock.

80
00:04:46,933 --> 00:04:49,367
Mulder, you weren't at Woodstock.

81
00:04:49,436 --> 00:04:51,404
I saw the movie.

82
00:04:58,511 --> 00:05:01,241
You all right by yourself?

83
00:05:01,348 --> 00:05:02,645
I'll be fine.

84
00:05:02,716 --> 00:05:04,183
I won't be long.

85
00:05:04,284 --> 00:05:05,546
Okay.

86
00:05:08,388 --> 00:05:12,620
(sighing)

87
00:05:12,692 --> 00:05:16,253
Hartley: Most of you here today
I know as neighbors

88
00:05:16,329 --> 00:05:19,594
and as cherished members
ofour Miracle Ministry.

89
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:23,295
But some ofyou have come
from far away...

90
00:05:23,370 --> 00:05:24,667
as far away

91
00:05:24,738 --> 00:05:25,864
as Pensacola, Florida...

92
00:05:25,939 --> 00:05:27,463
(cheering)

93
00:05:27,540 --> 00:05:29,804
and Uniondale, Long lsland!

94
00:05:29,909 --> 00:05:31,968
Wayne Ashtown and his family.

95
00:05:32,078 --> 00:05:35,047
And it is especially
to those ofyou

96
00:05:35,148 --> 00:05:36,911
who come from so far

97
00:05:36,983 --> 00:05:41,283
that I must apologize
from the bottom ofmy heart...

98
00:05:41,354 --> 00:05:43,117
because, unfortunately

99
00:05:43,189 --> 00:05:46,181
Samuel cannot be here
this afternoon.

100
00:05:46,259 --> 00:05:48,591
I know how very
deeply disappointed

101
00:05:48,662 --> 00:05:52,098
each and every one of you
must be feeling right now

102
00:05:52,165 --> 00:05:55,157
but I say unto you,
do not be dismayed.

103
00:05:55,235 --> 00:05:56,532
Do not despair!

104
00:05:56,603 --> 00:05:58,503
Do not lose your hope...

105
00:05:58,571 --> 00:06:02,632
because in two short days,
Samuel will be back here

106
00:06:02,709 --> 00:06:05,542
at our very special
miracle mission!

107
00:06:08,114 --> 00:06:10,742
Yes, indeed, praise God.

108
00:06:10,850 --> 00:06:12,784
Maybe we should head backstage

109
00:06:12,852 --> 00:06:15,082
and see what the reverend
has to say.

110
00:06:15,155 --> 00:06:17,919
Wait. This is where
they bring out Elvis.

111
00:06:17,991 --> 00:06:19,856
As these people will testify

112
00:06:19,926 --> 00:06:22,156
Samuel can heal you.

113
00:06:22,228 --> 00:06:25,254
Yes, Samuel will heal you.

114
00:06:25,331 --> 00:06:26,958
But...

115
00:06:28,702 --> 00:06:30,966
only if you believe.

116
00:06:33,473 --> 00:06:34,701
God bless you!

117
00:06:34,774 --> 00:06:37,572
Scully: Reverend Hartley,
we're with the FBl.

118
00:06:37,677 --> 00:06:40,441
I see Sheriff Daniels
has sent in the cavalry.

119
00:06:40,547 --> 00:06:42,481
We just want to talk to Samuel

120
00:06:42,549 --> 00:06:43,982
for a couple of minutes.

121
00:06:44,050 --> 00:06:45,278
He's not here.

122
00:06:45,351 --> 00:06:47,114
Mulder: Well, where is he?

123
00:06:47,187 --> 00:06:48,484
I don't know.

124
00:06:48,555 --> 00:06:50,250
I haven't seen him.

125
00:06:50,323 --> 00:06:52,689
That boy's been
a bit troubled lately.

126
00:06:52,759 --> 00:06:54,454
We're running late, Reverend.

127
00:06:54,527 --> 00:06:56,961
If you'll excuse me.

128
00:07:17,383 --> 00:07:18,645
Agent Mulder?

129
00:07:18,718 --> 00:07:19,707
Yeah.

130
00:07:19,819 --> 00:07:20,877
Sheriff Daniels.

131
00:07:20,954 --> 00:07:22,387
We spoke on the phone.

132
00:07:22,455 --> 00:07:24,548
This is Special Agent Dana Scully.

133
00:07:24,624 --> 00:07:27,388
You requested a copy
of the coroner's report.

134
00:07:27,460 --> 00:07:28,757
Right. Thankyou.

135
00:07:28,828 --> 00:07:30,227
I see you got a chance

136
00:07:30,296 --> 00:07:32,560
to take in
the Holy Roller sideshow.

137
00:07:32,632 --> 00:07:34,930
Something tells me
you're not a member

138
00:07:35,001 --> 00:07:36,559
of the reverend's fock.

139
00:07:36,636 --> 00:07:38,035
I remember Hartley

140
00:07:38,071 --> 00:07:39,766
when he was a soapbox preacher

141
00:07:39,839 --> 00:07:42,171
collecting dollar bills
in coffee cans.

142
00:07:42,242 --> 00:07:43,800
Since the boyjoined the act

143
00:07:43,910 --> 00:07:47,175
he's gotten himselfa Cadillac
for every day of the week

144
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:48,645
bought forwith money

145
00:07:48,715 --> 00:07:51,650
that should be used to improve
our roads and schools.

146
00:07:51,718 --> 00:07:53,151
People want to believe.

147
00:07:53,219 --> 00:07:55,949
99% of the people
in this world are fools

148
00:07:56,022 --> 00:07:59,549
and the rest ofus are
in great danger of contagion.

149
00:07:59,626 --> 00:08:01,719
Even if Hartley and Samuel are fakes

150
00:08:01,795 --> 00:08:03,126
it's still a long way

151
00:08:03,196 --> 00:08:04,959
from accusing the boy of murder.

152
00:08:05,031 --> 00:08:06,794
Witnesses say the boy was there

153
00:08:06,866 --> 00:08:09,664
laying hands on those people
when they died.

154
00:08:09,736 --> 00:08:12,830
You think that's how
he killed them, with a touch?

155
00:08:12,906 --> 00:08:14,339
I don't know how

156
00:08:14,407 --> 00:08:16,500
but we've been looking
for him since Tuesday

157
00:08:16,609 --> 00:08:18,839
and he does not want
to be found.

158
00:08:18,945 --> 00:08:21,345
There's nothing unusual
about these reports

159
00:08:21,414 --> 00:08:23,712
except that there were
no autopsies.

160
00:08:23,783 --> 00:08:25,774
Hartley blocked
my autopsy request

161
00:08:25,885 --> 00:08:27,182
on religious grounds.

162
00:08:27,253 --> 00:08:29,517
It doesn't help
that the county coroner

163
00:08:29,589 --> 00:08:31,454
is a member
of the Miracle Ministry.

164
00:08:31,524 --> 00:08:32,957
Maybe we can arrange

165
00:08:33,026 --> 00:08:35,153
to have them exhumed.

166
00:08:36,196 --> 00:08:38,164
to have them exhumed.

167
00:08:54,180 --> 00:08:56,205
Sheriff...

168
00:09:00,887 --> 00:09:02,912
It's Reverend Hartley's group.

169
00:09:03,022 --> 00:09:04,387
Damn.

170
00:09:04,457 --> 00:09:08,154
I told my people to keep quiet
so this wouldn't happen.

171
00:09:08,228 --> 00:09:10,992
Looks like you might have
a few believers

172
00:09:11,064 --> 00:09:12,326
on the payroll.

173
00:09:12,398 --> 00:09:15,492
Man: On behalf
of the Miracle Ministry

174
00:09:15,568 --> 00:09:19,129
we demand that you stop
this sacrilege.

175
00:09:19,205 --> 00:09:22,072
You're not just dealing
with me anymore, Vance.

176
00:09:22,141 --> 00:09:24,336
You're dealing with the FBl.

177
00:09:24,410 --> 00:09:28,244
We don't mean you any disrespect.

178
00:09:28,314 --> 00:09:30,748
We're investigating
a possible homicide.

179
00:09:30,817 --> 00:09:34,776
Federal law requires we do a postmortem
examination on these bodies.

180
00:09:34,854 --> 00:09:37,550
I'm afraid we answer
to a higher authority

181
00:09:37,657 --> 00:09:41,423
than the U.S. government--
one that considers grave digging

182
00:09:41,494 --> 00:09:43,724
and defiling corpses
mortal sins.

183
00:09:43,796 --> 00:09:46,162
Daniels: We'll get
that autopsy, Vance.

184
00:09:46,232 --> 00:09:48,496
Sooner or later,
you know we will.

185
00:09:48,568 --> 00:09:49,933
The deceased's family

186
00:09:50,003 --> 00:09:52,403
does not want
her grave disturbed.

187
00:09:52,472 --> 00:09:55,066
Carol Wallace had no family.

188
00:09:55,141 --> 00:09:57,268
We were her family.

189
00:09:59,145 --> 00:10:01,670
We were her family

190
00:10:01,748 --> 00:10:04,774
and it was hard enough
to bury her once.

191
00:10:04,851 --> 00:10:08,446
So if you insist
on going through with this

192
00:10:08,554 --> 00:10:10,522
we're prepared
to maintain a vigil

193
00:10:10,623 --> 00:10:14,525
and do whatever it takes
to stop you.

194
00:10:14,594 --> 00:10:16,289
Daniels: Mulder

195
00:10:16,362 --> 00:10:17,954
Scully...

196
00:10:19,866 --> 00:10:21,128
What?

197
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:25,466
One of my men just spotted
the boy's car downtown.

198
00:10:25,538 --> 00:10:27,403
Can't do much here.

199
00:10:27,473 --> 00:10:28,531
Mulder: Let's go.

200
00:10:45,358 --> 00:10:50,762
Daniels: Not a very likely place
to be saving souls.

201
00:11:04,277 --> 00:11:07,246
Where's the boy, Zook?

202
00:11:07,313 --> 00:11:08,871
He's in the can.

203
00:11:08,948 --> 00:11:10,381
What happened here?

204
00:11:10,450 --> 00:11:12,350
Damn fool started a fight.

205
00:11:12,418 --> 00:11:14,318
Figures them Bible thumpers

206
00:11:14,387 --> 00:11:18,551
wouldn't know how to hold their liquor.

207
00:11:18,658 --> 00:11:19,784
Where you been, Samuel?

208
00:11:19,892 --> 00:11:21,655
We've been looking for you.

209
00:11:21,728 --> 00:11:22,786
Yeah?

210
00:11:22,895 --> 00:11:24,362
I've been thinking.

211
00:11:24,430 --> 00:11:27,194
Well, you're going
to have plenty of time

212
00:11:27,266 --> 00:11:28,665
for that now, son.

213
00:11:28,735 --> 00:11:30,930
I'm putting you under arrest.

214
00:11:31,004 --> 00:11:33,666
For murder?

215
00:11:33,740 --> 00:11:35,264
For suspicion ofmurder.

216
00:11:35,341 --> 00:11:39,107
You mind if I finish my beer first?

217
00:11:39,178 --> 00:11:41,169
Well, you go right on ahead.

218
00:11:41,247 --> 00:11:44,580
I'm going to have somebody
take a statement from you.

219
00:11:44,650 --> 00:11:46,641
I'll see what I can do

220
00:11:46,719 --> 00:11:49,085
about getting your Caddie towed.

221
00:11:49,188 --> 00:11:50,348
Hey, Sheriff.

222
00:11:50,456 --> 00:11:51,980
What evidence do you have

223
00:11:52,091 --> 00:11:53,888
to charge the boy with murder?

224
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,518
Well, what more do you want?

225
00:11:55,628 --> 00:11:58,529
The boy's practically
given himself up.

226
00:11:58,598 --> 00:11:59,997
He's drunk, though.

227
00:12:00,066 --> 00:12:02,830
Well, then I'll add
drunk and disorderly.

228
00:12:02,902 --> 00:12:04,460
Let's get this straight.

229
00:12:04,537 --> 00:12:07,301
It's not a question
about the boy's guilt

230
00:12:07,373 --> 00:12:09,273
just how he did it.

231
00:12:09,342 --> 00:12:11,640
Let me have a minute with him?

232
00:12:11,711 --> 00:12:13,576
Suit yourself.

233
00:12:13,646 --> 00:12:16,012
Samuel, I'm Agent Mulder.

234
00:12:16,082 --> 00:12:18,141
This is Agent Scully.

235
00:12:18,217 --> 00:12:20,014
We're from the FBl.

236
00:12:20,086 --> 00:12:22,987
Looks like you took
quite a beating there.

237
00:12:23,089 --> 00:12:25,421
Penance, Mr. Mulder.

238
00:12:25,491 --> 00:12:28,255
Some might call it
a plain old bar brawl.

239
00:12:28,327 --> 00:12:30,420
You know what they say--

240
00:12:30,530 --> 00:12:33,158
" He giveth and He taketh away."

241
00:12:35,101 --> 00:12:36,625
Man gets too proud

242
00:12:36,702 --> 00:12:38,897
sometimes it does him good

243
00:12:38,971 --> 00:12:41,906
to get the crap
kicked out of him.

244
00:12:41,974 --> 00:12:43,874
Saves God the trouble.

245
00:12:43,943 --> 00:12:44,967
The trouble of what?

246
00:12:45,044 --> 00:12:47,444
Humbling the guilty sinner.

247
00:12:47,513 --> 00:12:49,174
Guilty of murder?

248
00:12:52,351 --> 00:12:53,545
Yes, sir.

249
00:12:53,619 --> 00:12:55,553
How did you do it, Samuel?

250
00:12:55,655 --> 00:12:58,215
Apparently,
my pride and my weakness

251
00:12:58,324 --> 00:13:00,656
were an invitation to the devil.

252
00:13:00,726 --> 00:13:03,661
I muddied the river
of my own faith.

253
00:13:03,729 --> 00:13:05,526
Now my gift has been corrupted.

254
00:13:05,598 --> 00:13:09,034
You're saying that you killed
those people with a touch?

255
00:13:09,102 --> 00:13:12,799
I've laid my hands on the ill,
given them health.

256
00:13:12,872 --> 00:13:14,464
I've healed the sick.

257
00:13:14,540 --> 00:13:19,273
I've even touched the dying
and given them life.

258
00:13:19,345 --> 00:13:22,337
God has given me a special gift.

259
00:13:22,415 --> 00:13:24,747
Did He buy you
all that jewelry too?

260
00:13:24,817 --> 00:13:27,183
Something is missing
in your story.

261
00:13:27,253 --> 00:13:29,517
Do you doubt
the power of God, ma'am?

262
00:13:29,622 --> 00:13:33,991
No, but I doubt
the veracity of your claims.

263
00:13:34,060 --> 00:13:37,689
I have looked on the infirm
and seen their sickness--

264
00:13:37,763 --> 00:13:39,355
their cancer.

265
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:44,326
just as I can see the pain

266
00:13:44,403 --> 00:13:46,303
on this man right here.

267
00:13:46,372 --> 00:13:47,430
Really?

268
00:13:47,507 --> 00:13:49,168
What pain is that?

269
00:13:52,745 --> 00:13:55,305
