784
00:39:58,509 --> 00:40:00,101
The man's delirious.

785
00:40:00,211 --> 00:40:01,872
He was here, Reverend.

786
00:40:01,979 --> 00:40:03,503
Right in this room...

787
00:40:03,614 --> 00:40:07,345
and he forgave me.

788
00:40:07,418 --> 00:40:10,478
(choking gasp)

789
00:40:17,729 --> 00:40:19,697
Scully: Rather than
simply killing Samuel

790
00:40:19,764 --> 00:40:22,858
Vance contrived to kill
the ministry's faith in him.

791
00:40:22,934 --> 00:40:24,561
We have conclusive evidence

792
00:40:24,635 --> 00:40:27,536
connecting him both
to the courtroom infestation

793
00:40:27,605 --> 00:40:29,266
and to the poisoning deaths

794
00:40:29,340 --> 00:40:31,535
ofthree members ofthe ministry.

795
00:40:32,877 --> 00:40:35,345
Vance's obsession
outlived Samuel however.

796
00:40:35,446 --> 00:40:38,813
His conscience haunted him
until he became delusory

797
00:40:38,883 --> 00:40:40,817
and finally took his own life

798
00:40:40,885 --> 00:40:43,376
effectively ending
our investigation.

799
00:40:43,454 --> 00:40:45,615
In light ofthis information

800
00:40:45,690 --> 00:40:47,157
it is highly doubtful

801
00:40:47,225 --> 00:40:49,955
that there have ever been
any miracles

802
00:40:50,027 --> 00:40:51,585
in Kenwood, Tennessee.

803
00:40:51,662 --> 00:40:53,960
(phone rings)

804
00:40:57,535 --> 00:40:59,730
Mulder.

805
00:40:59,804 --> 00:41:02,034
