816
00:41:28,099 --> 00:41:29,999
Talk sense, Deputy.

817
00:41:30,067 --> 00:41:32,729
She didn't exactly see
anyone taking the body.

818
00:41:32,804 --> 00:41:33,896
Well, what then?

819
00:41:33,971 --> 00:41:36,030
She, uh...

820
00:41:36,107 --> 00:41:38,940
she claims she saw Samuel
walking out by himself.

821
00:41:39,043 --> 00:41:44,037
Sounds crazy, I know,
but that's what she told me.

822
00:41:44,148 --> 00:41:45,843
You coming, Sheriff?

823
00:41:50,888 --> 00:41:52,947
I was drinking my coffee

824
00:41:53,024 --> 00:41:54,821
and going over the night orders

825
00:41:54,892 --> 00:41:57,190
for myward, seven south,

826
00:41:57,261 --> 00:41:58,922
when he walked right by me.

827
00:41:58,996 --> 00:42:01,123
His face was all black and blue.

828
00:42:01,199 --> 00:42:02,689
You're sure it was him.

829
00:42:02,767 --> 00:42:06,100
Well, at first I thought
my eyes were playing tricks

830
00:42:06,170 --> 00:42:08,832
which happens a lot on graveyard

831
00:42:08,906 --> 00:42:10,771
so I got up to look again

832
00:42:10,875 --> 00:42:12,502
but I lost him around a corner.

833
00:42:12,610 --> 00:42:15,272
Hejust vanished.

834
00:42:15,379 --> 00:42:16,846
Then I went to check the morgue

835
00:42:16,914 --> 00:42:19,075
and his bodywas gone.

836
00:42:19,150 --> 00:42:21,550
Daniels: This is insane.

837
00:42:21,619 --> 00:42:24,349
I won't listen to any more
ofthis crazy talk.

838
00:42:24,422 --> 00:42:26,913
I'm not the only one
who saw him, Sheriff

839
00:42:26,991 --> 00:42:28,618
so I know I'm not crazy.

840
00:42:28,693 --> 00:42:30,627
Other people saw him too.

841
00:42:35,066 --> 00:42:38,001
I'm not crazy.

842
00:42:38,069 --> 00:42:39,297
It was Samuel.

843
00:43:06,230 --> 00:43:09,961
Lillian: This isn't true,
Maurice, is it?

844
00:43:10,034 --> 00:43:11,797
The boywas an awful fake

845
00:43:11,869 --> 00:43:15,236
just likeyou said,
wasn't he, Maurice?

846
00:43:19,477 --> 00:43:21,172
Wasn't he, Maurice?

847
00:43:26,651 --> 00:43:28,778
(knocking)

848
00:43:37,428 --> 00:43:38,360
Sir...

849
00:43:38,429 --> 00:43:39,896
going to have to askyou

850
00:43:39,964 --> 00:43:41,192
to come with me.

851
00:43:41,265 --> 00:43:42,562
District Attorney

852
00:43:42,633 --> 00:43:44,567
wants to askyou
some questions

853
00:43:44,635 --> 00:43:46,830
concerning the boy's death.

854
00:43:52,410 --> 00:43:54,469
Sundays will probably
never be the same again

855
00:43:54,578 --> 00:43:55,875
in these parts.

856
00:43:55,947 --> 00:43:57,642
I have a strong sense
the Reverend Hartley

857
00:43:57,715 --> 00:43:59,774
is not going to be able
to give up the pulpit.

858
00:43:59,884 --> 00:44:01,875
Even without his son?

859
00:44:01,953 --> 00:44:04,285
Might even strengthen his faith.

860
00:44:04,355 --> 00:44:06,289
The boy did rise from the dead.

861
00:44:06,357 --> 00:44:09,349
That kind ofthing happens
only once or twice

862
00:44:09,427 --> 00:44:10,860
every 2,000 years or so.

863
00:44:10,928 --> 00:44:13,988
Yeah, and I have a story
about a plague oflocusts.

864
00:44:14,065 --> 00:44:15,726
I just hope Reverend Hartley

865
00:44:15,800 --> 00:44:17,768
didn't arrange his body snatching

866
00:44:17,835 --> 00:44:19,427
as his miracle ofmiracles.

867
00:44:19,503 --> 00:44:20,970
Somehow, I don't think so.

868
00:44:21,038 --> 00:44:22,596
What exactly doyou think?

869
00:44:22,673 --> 00:44:25,369
I think people
are looking hard for miracles.

870
00:44:25,476 --> 00:44:28,036
So hard that maybe
they make themselves see

871
00:44:28,145 --> 00:44:29,544
what theywant to see.

872
00:44:43,861 --> 00:44:46,455
You coming, Mulder?

873
00:45:40,284 --> 00:45:41,979
I made this.

